On Sunday, President William Ruto attended an Interdenominational church service in Nanyuki Stadium, Laikipia County. The President was accompanied by his deputy Rigathi Gachagua, Prime CS Musalia Mudavadi, alongside a host of other elected leaders including governors, senators, and MPs. Ruto has been in Laikipia since Thursday for a Cabinet retreat that ends on Sunday. The retreat included senior officials in the Executive, PSs and a meeting with Governors, the Senate and National Assembly representatives.